{
  "text": "In this model, initial continental crust is formed in island arcs (Fig. 3) , such as the Izu Bonin and Aleutians [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The required recycling may be caused by delamination processes. Structural interpretation of seismic profiles at oceanic arcs indicates tectonic separation by obduction of the upper layer and subduction of the lower layer in a crocodile tectonic structure [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] ; although in more mature continental crust other delamination processes may be important [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] .",
